<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-07-10T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-07-10T10:00:00-05:00" n="489" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d489">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/474: Telegram</note>
                                <head>
                                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                            State</gloss>
                                    </hi>
                                </head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                                        <placeName>
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-07-10T16:00:00+01:00">July 10, 1935—4 p.m.</date>
                                        <lb/> [Received July 10—2:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>232. Privately informed that the Secretary General has just
                                    received communication from Abyssinian representative at Paris
                                    requesting him to communicate to the members of the Council the
                                    breakdown of the arbitration procedures at Schweningen [<hi rend="italic">Scheveningen</hi>] and requesting that the
                                    Council as a matter of urgency consider the situation thus
                                    created.</p>
                                <p>This is informally interpreted as tantamount to a request for an
                                    early extraordinary meeting of the Council. League action,
                                    however, has not been determined upon.</p>
                                <p>This will probably be given to the press tomorrow.</p>
                                <closer>
                                    <signed>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gilbert</hi>
                                    </signed>
                                </closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>